"https:\/\/github.com\/lightningnetwork\/lnd\/releases\/tag\/v0.15.4-beta\">LND hotfix<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/ajtowns\/status\/1587414992961216512\">Anthony&#8217;s report<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/bitcoinmagazine.com\/technical\/exploiting-the-lightning-bug-was-ethical\">Shinobi&#8217;s Opinion<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>\ud83d\udcde Machankura<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Bitcoin in Africa via USSD feature phones that lack internet access.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/pretalx.com\/media\/adopting-bitcoin-2022\/submissions\/TN7E8E\/resources\/Adopting_Bitcoin_2022-1_SUFmFop.pdf\">Kgothatso&#8217;s slide deck from Adopting Bitcoin<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Unstructured_Supplementary_Service_Data\">Unstructured Supplementary Service Data<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>\ud83e\udd84 Rugpull Detection on Uniswap<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Researchers work on improved ways to detect rugpulls and other scams on the Uniswap protocol. 97.7% of the tokens in their dataset ended up being scams.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/arxiv.org\/pdf\/2201.07220.pdf\">Do Not Rug on Me: Zero-Dimensional Scam Detection<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>\ud83d\udd78 Running lightning in a web browser<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ben Carman uses LDK to make a web browser version of Mutiny wallet.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/BitcoinDevShop\/mutiny-web-poc\">Source Code<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/reckless.mutinywallet.com\/\">Web Wallet<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/benthecarman\/status\/1595395624010190850\">Ben&#8217;s Tweet<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/futurepaul\/status\/1595787240403501056\">Paul&#8217;s Trailer<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>0\ufe0f\u20e3 Full-RBF \/ Zero-Conf Debate<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ongoing debate over Full RBF and Bitcoin Core 24.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Antoine Riard raises issue about Lightning DoS attack by maliciously double-spending an input &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/lists.linuxfoundation.org\/pipermail\/lightning-dev\/2021-May\/003033.html\">[Lightning-dev] On Mempool Funny Games against Multi-Party Funded Transactions<\/a><\/li><li>Antoine Riard proposes Full RBF as a solution to the issue &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/lists.linuxfoundation.org\/pipermail\/bitcoin-dev\/2021-June\/019074.html\">[bitcoin-dev] Proposal: Full-RBF in Bitcoin Core 24.0<\/a><\/li><li>Antoine Riard creates a PR for Full RBF &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/bitcoin\/bitcoin\/pull\/25353\">Mempool Full RBF node setting PR<\/a><\/li><li>Dario Sneidermanis of Muun discusses that mempoolfullrbf may harm ZeroConf apps &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/lists.linuxfoundation.org\/pipermail\/bitcoin-dev\/2022-October\/020980.html\">[bitcoin-dev] [Opt-in full-RBF] Zero-conf apps in immediate danger<\/a><\/li><li>Suhas Daftuar opens a PR to remove <code>mempoolfullrbf<\/code> &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/bitcoin\/bitcoin\/pull\/26438\">Remove mempoolfullrbf option<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/bitcoin\/bitcoin\/releases\/tag\/v24.0\">Bitcoin Core 24 released<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>\ud83c\udff7 Slashtags<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/slashtags.to\/\">Slashtags Website<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/slashtags.to\/#playground\">Playground<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/slashtags.to\/technicals\">Technical Overview<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>\u26a1\ufe0f Channel Jamming Attacks<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/lists.linuxfoundation.org\/pipermail\/lightning-dev\/2022-November\/003740.html\">Clara&#8217;s mailing list post<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/s-tikhomirov\/ln-jamming-simulator\/blob\/master\/unjamming-lightning.pdf\">Unjamming Lightning: A Systematic Approach<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>It\u2019s almost time for&nbsp;Bitcoin Socratic Seminar #13! What is a Socratic Seminar? Inspired by other BitDevs meetups around the US, our Socratic Seminar events are forma